document_data.Abilities:
Giant-killers were known to be very agile fighters, skilled in targeting the weak points of their foes. Due to their narrow obsession with giants, they tended to be very knowledgeable about how to track down or sneak up on them, but also how to tailor their attacks to whichever race of giant they were facing. These tactics were also applicable to [[ogre]]s and [[troll]]s.

[[File:GiantKiller-2e.png|thumb|273px|A group of dwarves gather around a dwarven giant-killer and his latest slain giant in awe.]]
Many of the tactics that giant-killers in [[Faerun]] utilized were developed by [[shield dwarf]]s. On the isle of [[Oman]], giant-killers utilized techniques that were developed by [[Northlander]]s.{{Cite dragon/370/Adventurers of the Realms|38-39}}
